        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 20 at 12:08AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 1208 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 10 miles west of Vandervoort to 10 miles west
of Gillham to 10 miles west of Horatio to 11 miles southeast of
Broken Bow to 9 miles south of Idabel. Movement was northeast at 50
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Eagletown, Silver Ridge, Moon, Cerrogordo, Geneva, Watson, Central,
Goodwater, Shinewell, Muddy Fork, Haworth, America, Center Point,
Horatio, Provo, West Line, Corinth, Winthrop, Bellview, and Bokhoma.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for southwestern
Arkansas...southeastern Oklahoma...and northeastern Texas.</instruction>
